    "GRU: It is a type of RNN architecture that addresses the vanishing gradient problem and allows for capturing longterm dependencies in sequential data.",
    "It was introduced as an alternative to the traditional Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) units, offering a simpler and more computationally efficient design.",
    "GRU units consist of update and reset gates, which control the flow of information within the network."
